A Full, Robust, First-Principles Exploration
(State of the art as of mid-2026)
================================================================================
006.74 — Data mining / Knowledge representation / Metadata processing

1. CORE DEFINITIONS AND CONCEPTUAL FRAMING
------------------------------------------

Metadata          = data about data. Describes, contextualizes, locates, or
                    administers a primary resource (file, document, image,
                    dataset, note, code, etc.).

Metadata extraction = the automated (or semi-automated) process of identifying,
                      pulling, normalizing, and structuring that descriptive
                      information from a resource or its environment.

Tagging           = assigning discrete labels (keywords, categories, entities,
                    relations, controlled-vocabulary terms). Accurate tagging
                    is the high-value subset focused on findability, faceted
                    search, classification, and semantic linking.

Goal of automation: minimize human effort while maximizing
  • Precision (few false positives)
  • Recall (few missed relevant tags)
  • Consistency
  • Provenance / auditability
  • Scalability across heterogeneous content

Root problem: inference under uncertainty and heterogeneity.

