4. EXTRACTION TECHNIQUES — SPECTRUM
-----------------------------------

Rule-based / Pattern  →  Classical ML  →  Deep Learning  →  LLM/Generative  →  Hybrid + Human
(most auditable)                                                         (most flexible)


4.1 Rule-based & Heuristic
    Regex, XPath, layout templates, dictionaries, gazetteers, FSTs.
    High precision when stable; brittle on variation.
    Strength: full audit trail, zero hallucination, cheap, deterministic.
    Weakness: maintenance cost rises with heterogeneity.

4.2 Classical ML / Sequence Labeling
    CRF, HMM, SVM, Naïve Bayes for layout classification and field extraction.
    Still strong on homogeneous collections.

4.3 Deep Learning / Neural
    BiLSTM-CRF, Transformers, LayoutLM / DocLLM family (vision+text).
    Strong on complex visual layouts + text.

4.4 Large Language Models (2024–2026)
    Zero/few-shot, structured JSON output, tool-calling, agentic pipelines.
    Excellent at nuanced, multi-hop, domain-specific tagging.
    Risks: hallucination, inconsistency, cost, loss of provenance.
    Best use: LLM as proposer of candidates + high-precision validators.

4.5 Hybrid (Recommended for Accuracy)
    1. Deterministic first (filesystem, EXIF/IPTC/XMP, MIME, checksums)
    2. Content parsing + classical NER / keywords
    3. LLM or specialized model only for high-value/ambiguous fields
    4. Confidence scoring + thresholding + optional human review
    5. Feedback loop (corrections improve rules / fine-tunes / examples)

