7. CHALLENGES TO ACCURATE AUTOMATION
------------------------------------

• Heterogeneity of formats, layouts, languages, quality
• Ambiguity & context-dependence (right tags depend on use-case)
• Evolving standards and vocabularies
• Sparse or noisy signals
• Scale vs. depth trade-off
• Hallucination & run-to-run inconsistency (esp. pure LLM)
• Expensive ground truth; low inter-annotator agreement on subjective tags
• Provenance & trust requirements
• Maintenance burden (rules break, models drift, new types appear)
• Privacy / rights implications

Accuracy is multi-dimensional and use-case specific — not a single number.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

8. EVALUATION METRICS AND METHODOLOGY
-------------------------------------

Standard:
  Precision, Recall, F1 (per-tag or micro/macro)
  Exact vs. partial / hierarchical match
  Mean Average Precision (if ranked)

Practical additions:
  Coverage (% resources receiving useful metadata)
  Consistency across runs
  Human correction rate / edit distance
  Downstream utility (search NDCG, classification accuracy)
  Cost (compute, human time, latency)

Best practice: versioned gold-standard set, multiple annotators where subjective,
active learning, always report confidence calibration.

