9. BEST PRACTICES FOR ROBUST, ACCURATE SYSTEMS
----------------------------------------------

 1. Start with the deterministic layer — never skip technical metadata.
 2. Prefer hybrid over pure generative.
 3. Always emit provenance and confidence.
 4. Use controlled vocabularies + free tags (hybrid tagging).
 5. Normalize ruthlessly (ISO dates, canonical names, GeoJSON, etc.).
 6. Version everything (extractors, models, rules, prompts).
 7. Design for human override and feedback.
 8. Preserve alternative interpretations when ambiguity is high.
 9. Test on real, messy data early and often.
10. Document the application profile (what each field means in your context).
11. Separate extraction from storage so you can re-extract later.
12. Monitor drift (new file types, language change, model updates).

